<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-721-418  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 721 418.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  Oct 1989 v14 n10 p211(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Visually map your data. (Software Review ) (Mapping InformationSystems Corp. MapInfo 4.0) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miastkowski, Stan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Mapping Information Systems Corp's $750 MapInfo 4.0 is amicrocomputer-based geographic information system that ties a mapof a town, county, state, or country into the user's database andprovides a graphical representation of any sort or searchperformed.andP;  It lets users plot ASCII or dBASE III data onto any ofseveral hundred different maps and visualize 'what if' scenarios.andO;MapInfo requires at least 3Mbytes of hard disk space for theprogram itself and 2.2Mbytes for the national zip-code data file.andO;Its optional maps can take anywhere from 1Mbyte to 100Mbytes.andO;Each map consists of boundary, map, point, and image files.andP;  Theprogram lets the user integrate existing data into a map viaMBase, a dBASE III-compatible database manufactured by FoxBASE.andO;MapInfo is very resource-intensive, virtually demanding a fastprocessor and fast-access hard disk although it runs on anyDOS-based machine.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mapping Information Systems Corp. (manufactures).andO;Product:   MapInfo 4.0 (Geographic information system).andO;Topic:     Geographic information systemsMapsEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>